headline: Costco (COST) Is Up 6.5% After Surging January Sales And Digital Membership Gains - Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: In early February 2026, Costco Wholesale reported that January net sales rose to US$21.33 billion, up 9.3% year over year, with comparable sales and e-commerce volumes also increasing firmly across regions. Behind those headline figures, digitally enabled sales growth of over 34% and accelerating executive membership upgrades underscored how Costco’s membership model is powering its expanding online and in‑store ecosystems.
